Panamerican Games 1955 (Ciudad de México)

March 13 to 22.

13- 3 Mexico      1-1 Venezuela    
        [Gastón Monterola scored for Venezuela]   
13- 3 Argentina   2-1 Dutch Antilles        
        [Sanfilippo 20, Yudica 22;  R.De Lannoy 9]
14- 3 Argentina   5-0 Venezuela      
        [Pegnotti 2, 83, Sanfilippo 4, Menendez 44, Maschio 53]      
15- 3 Mexico      1-0 Dutch Antilles 
        [Rodriguez 55pen]     
16- 3 Venezuela   3-2 Dutch Antilles  
        [Pedro Díaz 13pen, Gastón Monterola 33, 46; H.Schoop 4, 20]   
16- 3 Argentina   3-0 Mexico     
        [Sanfilippo (2), Clariá]    
18- 3 Mexico      3-3 Venezuela     
        [Gastón Monterola, Antonio Rodríguez, Bosco (og) scored 
         for Venezuela] 
18- 3 Argentina   4-2 Dutch Antilles    
        [Sanfilippo 10, 16, ?, Yudica 80; G. Bernadina 33,
         R.de Lannoy 46]
20- 3 Mexico      2-3 Dutch Antilles  
        [? 15, Noriega 63; W.Heyliger 16, M.Bicentini 55, R.Kemp 85]
20- 3 Argentina   6-1 Venezuela       
        [Sanfilippo (3), Maschio, Pérsico; Campana; Pedro Díaz]   
21- 3 Venezuela   1-3 Dutch Antilles
        [Antonio Rodríguez 57; M.Bicentini 12, 20, H.Schoop 28]  
22- 3 Argentina   3-3 Mexico               
        [Maschio, Scialino, Campana; Mercado, González, Martínez]

 1.ARGENTINA     6  5  1  0  23- 7  11 
 2.Mexico        6  1  3  2  10-13   5 
 3.D. Antilles   6  2  0  4  11-13   4  
 4.Venezuela     6  1  2  3   9-20   4


Additional Match Details

13/03/1955  Ciudad de México Mexico XI          1-1   Venezuela          Panamerican G
Estadio “de la Ciudad universitaria” 10000
Mercado 15’ / Monterola 75’
Mex: Sánchez; Carrillo, Rodríguez; Colmenero, Arieta, Pérez; Vargas, Díaz, Noriega, Mercado,
Negrete.
Ven: Franklin; Vera, Medina; Lascuarain, Heredia, Matson; Gonzalito, Alterio, Iraquez, Tovar,
Monterola.
Ref: John Best (USA).

13/03/1955  Ciudad de México Argentina XI       2-1   Netherlands Antil. Panamerican G
DUTCH ANTILLES
E. Hato; P. Matrona - W. de Lannoy (W. Canword); M. Bicentini - C. Adoptie -
G. Giribaldi; W. Heyliger - R. de Lannoy - H. Schoop - G. Bernadina (H.Hoek)
- J. Jansen
(Due to injury P. Matrona had to leave the game after 70 minutes and Dutch
Ant. continued with 10 players)
ARGENTINA
Bevilacqua; Anido (c) - Castillo; Malazzo - Claria - Pegnotti; Scialino (Serico)
- Molina (Campana) - Menendez - Sanfilippo - Yudica
Referee:        Prudencio Garcia (U.S.A.)

14/03/1955  Ciudad de México Argentina XI       5-0   Venezuela          Panamerican G
HT 3-0, Estadio Monumental de la Ciudad Universitaria, 10000
Goals: Pegnotti 2’ 83’, San Filippo 4’, Menéndez 44’, Maschio 53’
Arg: Bevilacqua; Anido, Castillo; Malazzo, Claria, Pegnotti; Scialino, Campana (Maschio 46’),
Menéndez, San Filippo, Yudica.
Ven: Franklin; Matson, Medina, Vera; Heredia, Altrio; Gonzalito, Rodríguez, Manterola
(Landaiz 40’), Tovar, Iraquez.
Ref: John Best (USA).
“Argentina used three subs, Venezuela two”.

